news.title: Residents of 27 villages protest against property tax hike by Kalyan-Dombivli civic body
news.para: The protest was led by 27 Ganv Sangharsh Samiti president Gangaram Shelar and vice president Gulab Vaze. Vaze said that after 27 villages were included in KDMC, they have increased property tax at least 10 times but have not given any services in these villages.

news.title: Construction waste to be collected in Jaipur soon
news.para: According to an estimate, every day around 300 metric tons of CND waste is generated here that is dumped on the roadside.

news.title: Punjab cabinet approves Rs 5.50 per cubic ft rates for sand, gravel
news.para: ​​According to the policy, sand and gravel will be provided to the public at Rs 5.5 per cubic feet at mining sites, including loading charges. ​​Further, the royalty rate of ordinary clay and ordinary earth shall be decreased from Rs 10 per tonne to Rs 2.50 per tonne.

news.title: Beneficiaries receive flats under LIFE mission in Thiruvananthapuram
news.para: ​The complex was constructed on 20 cents of land. The total budget was Rs 3.23 crores with Venganoor panchayat spending Rs 2.53 crores and district panchayat shelling out Rs 70 lakhs.

news.title: Mardas HC seeks report on petition to prevent illegal sand mining
news.para: In his petition, P Ashok Kumar stated that there are several acres of vacant land parcels at Periyammapatti village in Palani taluk which belong to the government.

news.title: Now pay property tax via credit or debit card in Dehradun
news.para: The civic body on Monday started the facility of making digital payments at its office. Earlier, only cash and cheques were accepted.

news.title: Gurugram development body plans Rs 1,000 per sq metre fine for green belt encroachers
news.para: At a recent GMDA Core Planning Cell (CPC) meeting, officials proposed that some regulations are required to protect the city’s green belt.

news.title: Legitimate residents to get 300 sq ft plots in Aurangabad
news.para: Authorities said that the people’s representatives have assured 130 families, which are considered to be legitimate residents of these colonies, will get 300 square feet of land in the Padegaon or Harsul area.

news.title: IFS officer refuses to probe illegal constructions in Corbett Tiger Reserve
news.para: ​Meanwhile, another IFS officer BK Gangtey, who was also asked to probe the same matter by another authority, also raised objections to his appointment as inquiry officer.

news.title: Vadodara: Builder cheated of Rs 1 crore by business partners in Waghodiya
news.para: The builder Prashant Trivedi lodged a complaint of cheating and forgery at Waghodiya police station on Monday after the partners Sunil Makhija and his brother Deepak Makhija did not return his money and sold off the properties promised to him to others.

news.title: China: Shares of Fantasia Holdings halve as trade resumes; misses bond payment
news.para: "Given the liquidity issue faced by the Group, there is no guarantee that the Group will be able to meet its financial obligations under its other financing documents," Fantasia Holdings said in the filing.

news.title: Gurugram civic body eyes revenue from building plan approvals
news.para: Additional commissioner Vaishali Sharma said on Tuesday that the aim of the survey is to prevent the construction of unauthorised buildings at the initial stages itself.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP sets up five teams to inspect sites for building violations
news.para: These teams, led by junior engineers, will inspect sites twice after the grant of OC — first within 10 days and the second within 45 days — and will report to the office of the district town planner.

news.title: Godrej & Boyce to retain 3,401 acres on business division
news.para: Of the 3,401 acres located in the eastern suburbs of Mumbai, roughly 1,750 acres of mangroves are part of the Soonabai Pirojsha Godrej Foundation.

news.title: Japan's Marubeni, Wadhwa Group in talks for real estate investment platform
news.para: The Wadhwa Group is eyeing redevelopment of old and dilapidated tenanted projects in India’s commercial capital as a growth opportunity for the company.
